title: Be careful when you go to return items
text: I do like this app although it is pretty much low quality things that 50% of the time don‚Äôt do what they say they‚Äôll do. Also, I don‚Äôt like how they‚Äôre getting people to give it 5 stars on the app stores , so other people might see their review and use their referral code when signing up. That‚Äôs shady business but the reason I‚Äôm giving it 1 star is because I had multiple items in one shipment that didn‚Äôt work or the description was inaccurate and they sent me a confusing offer that I thought meant I ‚Äúcould pay $10 and keep everything I wanted to return and receive my refund (around $50) as well.‚Äù But they got me, because what they meant was (well give you $10 for your $50 worth of stuff and you get to keep everything)‚Ä¶ well, that‚Äôd be fine if the digital scale a bought worked or came with instructions or the usb wireless display dongle actually worked‚Ä¶ or the two storage containers I bought for under my bed were only 2‚Äù high once I finally put them together which isn‚Äôt big enough to hold anything worth storing under my bed. When I asked customer service if I could immediately change that back after I realize what it was they just quickly and poorly told me that it‚Äôs too late. It‚Äôs already been done. Honestly I don‚Äôt care. It‚Äôs just junk but I‚Äôm hoping this review can make it through all the other fraudulent five star reviews and help somebody out in the process
